.TH "KENNEL-POLICY" "1" "" "Project Kennel" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
kennel\-policy \- author, inspect, compile, and check Project Kennel policies (the leaf house)
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBkennel policy\fR \fIsub-verb\fR [\fIargs\fR...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBkennel policy\fR is the policy\-authoring noun group of \fBkennel\fR(1). A policy is a TOML file (see \fBpolicy.toml\fR(5)) that inherits from a signed template chain and may compose signed fragments. These sub\-verbs resolve, check, and compile policies; none of them need the \fBkenneld\fR(8) daemon. The shared bases a policy inherits from — templates and fragments — are managed by their own noun group, \fBkennel\-template\fR(1).
.PP
Compilation resolves the inheritance chain and includes, verifies every referenced artefact's signature and lockfile pin, and emits a signed settled artefact that the daemon enforces at \fBkennel run\fR time.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
\fBkennel policy list\fR
list policies in the search path
.TP
\fBkennel policy show <policy> [\-\-template\-dir D]... [\-\-trust\-dir D]...\fR
show what a policy resolves to (the effective policy)
.RS
.TP
\fB\-\-template\-dir D\fR
Add a directory to the template/fragment search path (repeatable). Overrides the config.toml default cascade.
.RE
.RS
.TP
\fB\-\-trust\-dir D\fR
Add a directory to the signing\-key trust store used while authoring (repeatable).
.RE
.TP
\fBkennel policy edit <name>\fR
edit a policy's source in $EDITOR
.TP
\fBkennel policy generate <name> [\-\-from <template>]\fR
scaffold a new leaf policy
.RS
.TP
\fB\-\-from <template>\fR
Scaffold the leaf from this template (default base\-confined).
.RE
.TP
\fBkennel policy compile <policy> [\-\-output P] [\-\-key K | \-\-unsigned] [\-\-key\-id ID] [\-\-require\-signed] [\-\-no\-lock] [\-\-template\-dir D]... [\-\-trust\-dir D]...\fR
compile a source policy into a signed settled artefact
.RS
.TP
\fB\-\-output P\fR
Write the settled artefact to P.
.RE
.RS
.TP
\fB\-\-key K\fR
Sign the settled artefact with key K.
.RE
.RS
.TP
\fB\-\-unsigned\fR
Emit an unsigned artefact (mutually exclusive with \-\-key).
.RE
.RS
.TP
\fB\-\-require\-signed\fR
Fail unless every referenced artefact is signed.
.RE
.RS
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-lock\fR
Do not read or write the kennel.lock pin file.
.RE
.RS
.TP
\fB\-\-template\-dir D\fR
Add a directory to the template/fragment search path (repeatable). Overrides the config.toml default cascade.
.RE
.RS
.TP
\fB\-\-trust\-dir D\fR
Add a directory to the signing\-key trust store used while authoring (repeatable).
.RE
.TP
\fBkennel policy validate <policy> [\-\-require\-signed] [\-\-template\-dir D]... [\-\-trust\-dir D]...\fR
resolve and check a policy without writing an artefact
.RS
.TP
\fB\-\-require\-signed\fR
Fail unless every referenced artefact is signed.
.RE
.RS
.TP
\fB\-\-template\-dir D\fR
Add a directory to the template/fragment search path (repeatable). Overrides the config.toml default cascade.
.RE
.RS
.TP
\fB\-\-trust\-dir D\fR
Add a directory to the signing\-key trust store used while authoring (repeatable).
.RE
.TP
\fBkennel policy risks <policy> [\-\-template\-dir D]... [\-\-trust\-dir D]... [\-\-json]\fR
evaluate a policy against the threat catalogue (exposures, residuals)
.RS
.TP
\fB\-\-json\fR
Emit the structured report (for CI/tooling) instead of the human view.
.RE
.RS
.TP
\fB\-\-template\-dir D\fR
Add a directory to the template/fragment search path (repeatable). Overrides the config.toml default cascade.
.RE
.RS
.TP
\fB\-\-trust\-dir D\fR
Add a directory to the signing\-key trust store used while authoring (repeatable).
.RE
.TP
\fBkennel policy diff <policy> [<other>] [\-\-template\-dir D]... [\-\-trust\-dir D]... [\-\-json]\fR
interpreted grant delta between a policy and its baseline (or another policy)
.RS
.TP
\fB\-\-json\fR
Emit the structured delta (for CI/tooling) instead of the human view.
.RE
.RS
.TP
\fB\-\-template\-dir D\fR
Add a directory to the template/fragment search path (repeatable). Overrides the config.toml default cascade.
.RE
.RS
.TP
\fB\-\-trust\-dir D\fR
Add a directory to the signing\-key trust store used while authoring (repeatable).
.RE
.TP
\fBkennel policy inspect <policy> \-\-unix [\-\-template\-dir D]... [\-\-trust\-dir D]...\fR
inspect grants in a settled policy (\-\-unix: AF_UNIX sockets)
.RS
.TP
\fB\-\-unix\fR
Show AF_UNIX socket grants (§7.6).
.RE
.RS
.TP
\fB\-\-template\-dir D\fR
Add a directory to the template/fragment search path (repeatable). Overrides the config.toml default cascade.
.RE
.RS
.TP
\fB\-\-trust\-dir D\fR
Add a directory to the signing\-key trust store used while authoring (repeatable).
.RE
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
\fB0\fR
Success. For kennel run, the workload's own exit code is passed through (clamped to a byte).
.TP
\fB1\fR
Generic failure: the CLI could not reach kenneld, a file could not be read, or kenneld returned an error.
.TP
\fB3\fR
Policy validation or resolution failure: schema, invariants, template inheritance, or include conflict.
.TP
\fB6\fR
Signature or lockfile\-pin failure during resolution.
.TP
\fB7\fR
kennel policy lint found at least one coherence finding across the template corpus.
.SH FILES
.TP
\fIkennel.lock\fR
The lockfile beside a leaf policy: pins the SHA\-256 of every resolved reference.
.TP
\fI~/.config/kennel/keys/\fR
User signing\-key store (run policies; not templates). See config.toml(5).
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
\fBkennel policy generate myjob \-\-from ai\-coding\-strict\fR
Scaffold a new leaf policy from a template.
.TP
\fBkennel policy validate myjob\fR
Resolve and check it without writing an artefact.
.TP
\fBkennel policy compile myjob \-\-key my\-key\-2026\fR
Compile and sign a settled artefact.
.SH SEE ALSO
\fBkennel\fR(1), \fBkennel\-template\fR(1), \fBpolicy.toml\fR(5), \fBkenneld\fR(8)
